{
  "_instructions": [
    "Purpose: This file drives a simple GLP-1 coverage-pathway display. It is not a clinical guideline and not a substitute for verifying the member-specific benefit, formulary, and current payer policy.",
    "Do not infer across payer_id or plan_type_id. The application should only display a policy when payer_id + plan_type_id match exactly.",
    "Arrange each exact payer/plan policy as a list of agents. Each agent may have multiple pathways because one drug may be covered for diabetes, obesity, cardiovascular risk reduction, CKD, or OSA under different rules.",
    "Every pathway must use one of these status values: covered_no_prior_authorization, covered_with_conditions_no_authorization, covered_with_authorization, covered_with_authorization_and_prior_trials, not_covered.",
    "Use covered_no_prior_authorization only when the source explicitly says the drug is covered without authorization and without chart criteria beyond normal prescribing. Use covered_with_conditions_no_authorization when coverage is available without authorization only if specific diagnosis/lab/indication criteria are present.",
    "Use covered_with_authorization when the payer requires authorization but not an explicit prior medication trial. Use covered_with_authorization_and_prior_trials when both authorization criteria and prior therapy/failure/contraindication are required.",
    "Put diagnosis/lab/indication requirements in pathway.criteria. Put step therapy, preferred product, metformin, lifestyle program, or prior medication requirements in pathway.prior_trials.",
    "criteria and prior_trials support all_of and any_of. References must point to criteria_library IDs. Example: {\"all_of\":[\"type_2_diabetes\"],\"any_of\":[\"a1c_ge_6_5\",\"fpg_ge_126\"]}.",
    "criteria_library.search_terms is the source for the Epic search block. Terms should be specific chart-finding terms, not prose. Keep them short and pasteable.",
    "When deep research is completed, replace sample policies with exact, cited payer policies. Include source_url, source_name, effective_date, retrieved_date, and verification_status for every policy."
  ],
  "schema_version": "2.0-pathways",
